The paper discusses the empirical analysis of Web traffic patterns and proposes a new navigation model based on individual bookmark lists. This work involves the study of user behavior and interaction with the Web, which falls under the sub-categories of Social and Information Retrieval (cs.SI), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper also discusses the impact of browser features on Web traffic, which could be related to Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Software Engineering (cs.SD).
